g.text: Inequality (Gini coefficient), based on individual income or in some cases, consumption. Higher means more inequality.
Higher inequality countries have more homicides.
Source: World Bank, World Development Indicators, series VC.IHR.PSRC.P5 and SI.POV.GINI. Analysis by freerangestats.info.
